race.comment: CUESTA (6) presents third up for the Bjorn Baker yard and is ready to show her best. Last preparation, she just missed in a couple of strong provincial Maidens, and she's on a 7-day backup. Bullock is a positive jockey engagement and trust in him to manage the awkward gate. ALABAMA HUSSY (4) peaks off a 2L defeat at Hawkesbury. Needs to find a bit more to win but will get every chance. GO ZOLA (7) resumes, and the betting moves should be monitored with her. May need one but has decent ability and draws an inside gate. CATHEDRAL COVE (1) looks to be building into his campaign nicely and can make his presence felt third-up.
